1
00:02:06,746 --> 00:02:09,841
Why Emmet Ray?
Because he was interesting.

2
00:02:09,917 --> 00:02:12,579
To me, Emmet Ray was
a fascinating character.

3
00:02:12,652 --> 00:02:15,213
I was a huge fan of his
when I was younger.

4
00:02:15,289 --> 00:02:18,258
I thought he was
an absolutely great guitar player...

5
00:02:18,327 --> 00:02:20,262
and he was funny.

6
00:02:20,330 --> 00:02:22,264
You know, or...

7
00:02:22,332 --> 00:02:25,392
if funny's the wrong word,
then sort of pathetic in a way.

8
00:02:25,468 --> 00:02:29,131
He was flamboyant
and he was, you know...

9
00:02:29,204 --> 00:02:31,436
boorish and obnoxious.

10
00:02:31,509 --> 00:02:35,000
Well, the problem is that there's
just so little known about him.

11
00:02:35,078 --> 00:02:38,243
But we do know that
he was a great guitar player.

12
00:02:38,316 --> 00:02:42,686
I'd say he was probably the second
greatest guitar player in the world.

13
00:02:42,755 --> 00:02:44,689
Django Reinhardt was the best...

14
00:02:44,756 --> 00:02:47,455
and believe me,
Emmet idolized Django.

15
00:02:47,529 --> 00:02:49,258
He was in awe of him.

16
00:02:49,330 --> 00:02:53,789
There's a story that says when he
saw him playing in France, he fainted.

17
00:02:53,868 --> 00:02:59,330
He saw Django again at a restaurant
in Germany, and he fainted again.

18
00:02:59,407 --> 00:03:01,069
It seems that every time...

19
00:03:01,143 --> 00:03:04,271
Django would always make him faint
or he'd make him cry.

20
00:03:05,015 --> 00:03:08,574
Well, his relationship with Hattie
is mostly what's known about him.

21
00:03:08,650 --> 00:03:11,621
There are a few Emmet Ray
stories before that...

22
00:03:11,688 --> 00:03:14,589
but I have no idea whether
they're true or not.

23
00:03:14,658 --> 00:03:17,458
First time anybody seemed
to have heard of him was in Chicago.

24
00:03:17,529 --> 00:03:19,792
It was at this roadside joint.

25
00:03:23,936 --> 00:03:26,132
Good to see you tonight.

26
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:31,303
- Where the hell is he?
- I don't know.

27
00:03:31,380 --> 00:03:33,938
You gotta get him, Dan.
He's layin' drunk somewhere.

28
00:03:34,015 --> 00:03:37,178
- He's probably in a poolroom.
- Every night it's somethin' else.

29
00:03:37,252 --> 00:03:40,277
He's late. He gets drunk.
He falls off the bandstand.

30
00:03:40,354 --> 00:03:43,449
- I told you not to hire this guy.
- What time does Emmet Ray go on?

31
00:03:43,526 --> 00:03:46,086
Look at the crowd.
Think they're here to see me?

32
00:03:46,161 --> 00:03:47,858
Relax. I'll find him.

33
00:03:47,931 --> 00:03:50,297
I'm gonna have to
hold the show again.

34
00:03:50,366 --> 00:03:52,960
I'll kill this guy.
I don't care what kind of artist he is.

35
00:03:53,035 --> 00:03:56,268
You take care of business.
I'll find him. Just relax.

36
00:03:57,342 --> 00:03:59,539
Hey, good to see you again.

37
00:04:02,714 --> 00:04:04,308
That's 50 more you owe me.

38
00:04:04,384 --> 00:04:08,047
I'm not goin' out of town.
Another one?

39
00:04:10,859 --> 00:04:13,052
I think you got some visitors.

40
00:04:15,029 --> 00:04:16,792
I'll be back.

41
00:04:20,669 --> 00:04:23,104
- What'd we get?
- Here's your end.

42
00:04:28,678 --> 00:04:32,207
This is what you bring me, $30?
It's almost midnight. $30?

43
00:04:32,284 --> 00:04:34,218
That's half, Emmet.
That's all we made.

44
00:04:34,285 --> 00:04:37,416
I can't live on that.
I got car payments, I got new shirts.

45
00:04:37,491 --> 00:04:40,549
I'm sorry. Business was slow.
It's a Jewish holiday.

46
00:04:40,625 --> 00:04:44,653
And last night it was rainin', and
the night before you got food poisonin'.

47
00:04:44,730 --> 00:04:47,790
- Because I drank that booze you made.
- Listen, Emmet.

48
00:04:47,867 --> 00:04:51,201
I don't know how to tell you this,
but while I was in bed...

49
00:04:51,272 --> 00:04:56,641
with one of the johns you sent me,
he got very excited, and he...

50
00:04:56,710 --> 00:04:59,944
got a heart attack,
and he dropped dead.

51
00:05:01,417 --> 00:05:04,444
- Which one?
- The salesman from Detroit.

52
00:05:04,521 --> 00:05:08,183
- What did you do?
- I took my clothes and I left.

53
00:05:08,257 --> 00:05:10,784
So there's nothin'
to trace back to us?

54
00:05:10,860 --> 00:05:15,058
Then I was thinking that maybe
he had one of your business cards.

55
00:05:16,134 --> 00:05:19,298
- Oh, my God.
- A pimp doesn't need business cards!

56
00:05:19,372 --> 00:05:21,306
You're always tryin'
to be too fancy.

57
00:05:21,374 --> 00:05:24,342
Emmet, let's go.
You're supposed to be on stage.

58
00:05:24,410 --> 00:05:27,641
Every night you're either late,
drunk, or you don't show up.

59
00:05:27,714 --> 00:05:29,944
What is it with you?

60
00:05:41,530 --> 00:05:44,864
How are you doin'?
I'm on right now.

61
00:05:44,935 --> 00:05:47,527
Thanks for comin'.
Put their tab on my bill.

62
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:52,172
I don't wanna embarrass you in front of
friends, but boss said no more advances.

63
00:05:52,243 --> 00:05:55,441
Don't give me a song and dance.
Just put their tab on my bill.

64
00:05:55,514 --> 00:05:57,243
Hi, guys.

65
00:08:22,786 --> 00:08:26,415
It's gonna be a lot of cats there.
We always have fun at Don's.

66
00:08:26,490 --> 00:08:28,583
- Donald.
- Well, Donald.

67
00:08:28,658 --> 00:08:30,592
- Watch out over there.
- I got this, man.

68
00:08:30,661 --> 00:08:33,097
You take care of that.
And don't forget to pass.

69
00:08:33,165 --> 00:08:36,292
- They caught him a couple of times.
- Caught what?

70
00:08:36,367 --> 00:08:39,167
Mind your business.
Watch the road.

71
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,570
What you got there, man?
Is that a.45?

72
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:44,042
.45 what?
Wait, wait.

73
00:08:45,345 --> 00:08:47,370
Better put that shit away.

74
00:08:47,447 --> 00:08:50,977
Hey, you wanna go to the dump,
shoot some rats? Huh?

75
00:08:51,053 --> 00:08:53,316
- Shoot some what?
- Rats.

76
00:08:53,388 --> 00:08:56,255
I do it all the time.
It's a lot of fun.

77
00:08:56,325 --> 00:09:00,228
- A hepcat shootin' rats.
- I don't think you need no more of this.

78
00:09:00,296 --> 00:09:04,994
There should be no other guns
in this car besides my gun.

79
00:09:22,255 --> 00:09:24,689
Man, where'd you learn
to play that thing like that?

80
00:09:24,758 --> 00:09:28,662
- I never heard guitar sound so good.
- Yeah, I'm the greatest in the world.

81
00:09:28,731 --> 00:09:31,220
Well, you know,
in France there's Django.

82
00:09:31,299 --> 00:09:35,326
Django? You know, he's comin'
to America in the summer to record.

83
00:09:35,404 --> 00:09:38,636
- Yeah?
- Yeah. Ever meet him?

84
00:09:38,708 --> 00:09:41,232
I could've once, in Europe.

85
00:09:41,311 --> 00:09:44,074
You know, really,
our styles are just different.

86
00:09:44,148 --> 00:09:47,741
Nate Drummond prefers me.
He says I'm miraculous.

87
00:09:47,816 --> 00:09:51,777
You're welcome to come here anytime.
You know, we play here all the time.

88
00:09:51,856 --> 00:09:54,654
- And I make great chili.
- Well, thank you.

89
00:10:12,814 --> 00:10:15,646
Say, man, we're about to hit it.
Can we drop you somewhere?

90
00:10:15,716 --> 00:10:18,084
- I like the air. I'll walk.
- You sure about that?

91
00:10:18,154 --> 00:10:20,087
Yeah. Thank you.

92
00:10:48,755 --> 00:10:51,658
Well, I heard stories
that he was a kleptomaniac.

93
00:10:51,727 --> 00:10:55,664
I heard that once he stole
an alarm clock from Hoagy Carmichael...

94
00:10:55,731 --> 00:10:58,529
and Hoagy overslept
and he missed a record date.

95
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:00,192
What do you think?

96
00:11:00,269 --> 00:11:04,764
The only other story that I heard,
other than Hattie, was this moon idea.

97
00:11:04,841 --> 00:11:08,334
He had this idea
about this crescent moon.

98
00:11:08,412 --> 00:11:11,471
That he wanted to make an entrance
on this big crescent moon.

99
00:11:11,547 --> 00:11:14,917
Well, the story is that
it came to him, apparently...

100
00:11:14,986 --> 00:11:17,181
I guess, in a dream...

101
00:11:17,255 --> 00:11:19,749
that he'd build this moon thing
with his own money.

102
00:11:19,826 --> 00:11:22,521
Because he thought that
a star of his great stature...

103
00:11:22,595 --> 00:11:26,430
ought to be able to make
a real big entrance with a moon.

104
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,613
Just try to visualize it.

105
00:11:27,614 --> 00:11:28,729
Just try to visualize it.

106
00:11:28,803 --> 00:11:32,000
You're lookin' up, and there it is.
Gold, beautiful moon.

107
00:11:32,073 --> 00:11:35,339
I'm comin' down, and you guys
are playin'. What do you think?

108
00:11:35,411 --> 00:11:38,573
It's a stupid idea. I told you.
Would you let me take this shot?

109
00:11:38,646 --> 00:11:42,176
I didn't ask your opinion.
I'm just tellin' you how it's gonna go.

110
00:11:52,329 --> 00:11:55,458
And then the jacket
would match the moon...

111
00:11:55,534 --> 00:11:58,663
against a black
velvet background.

112
00:11:58,738 --> 00:12:01,969
- What do you think?
- It sounds okay to me.

113
00:12:02,041 --> 00:12:04,202
- Yeah.
- It's fancy.

114
00:12:05,678 --> 00:12:08,410
I'm considered
the best guitar player...

115
00:12:08,483 --> 00:12:10,451
maybe that ever lived.

116
00:12:12,019 --> 00:12:14,455
Certainly in this country.
There's this...

117
00:12:14,523 --> 00:12:17,012
There's a gypsy in France...

118
00:12:17,091 --> 00:12:20,550
and he's the most
beautiful thing I ever heard.

119
00:12:22,598 --> 00:12:24,192
Tonight's the night.

120
00:12:24,268 --> 00:12:27,998
Emmet, just as long as you're happy.
That's the most important thing.

121
00:12:28,071 --> 00:12:29,664
It's really beautiful.

122
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:32,538
It is really beautiful.
It's like jewelry.

123
00:12:34,314 --> 00:12:38,146
Hey, I wanna just be alone with
the moon for a minute, all right?

124
00:12:38,216 --> 00:12:41,186
You wanna be alone
with the moon? Okay.

125
00:12:41,254 --> 00:12:44,188
Emmet, you know what you are?
You're a genius.

126
00:12:59,808 --> 00:13:02,211
She's a knockout, ain't she?

127
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:04,008
Hope it's safe.

128
00:13:05,015 --> 00:13:08,145
Of course it's safe.
Why wouldn't it be safe?

129
00:13:08,219 --> 00:13:12,485
It's a hell of a drop.
A man can break his neck.

130
00:13:13,359 --> 00:13:15,189
Really?

131
00:13:15,260 --> 00:13:19,289
And it starts to build and build
in Emmet's mind.

132
00:13:19,366 --> 00:13:21,798
And by show time...

133
00:13:21,866 --> 00:13:25,133
he's numb with fear,
he's petrified.

134
00:13:25,205 --> 00:13:28,140
And the audience is out there
waiting for him...

135
00:13:28,208 --> 00:13:31,475
and he's backstage, meanwhile,
drinking and drinking.

136
00:13:31,546 --> 00:13:35,177
When he's ready to go on,
he's stiff as a board.

137
00:13:38,153 --> 00:13:40,589
- Snazzy!
- Did you buy that off the rack?

138
00:13:42,326 --> 00:13:44,259
Look. The Big Dipper.

139
00:13:44,327 --> 00:13:48,286
- Emmet, your gun is bulging.
- Do you think?

140
00:13:48,364 --> 00:13:50,389
What the hell you
need it on stage for?

141
00:13:50,466 --> 00:13:52,459
I don't feel right
without it.

142
00:13:52,537 --> 00:13:54,971
I'll give it back to you
as soon as you're done.

143
00:13:55,039 --> 00:13:57,100
Show time!

144
00:14:14,264 --> 00:14:16,788
- You all right?
- Emmet, be careful.

145
00:14:23,639 --> 00:14:24,903
You're on?

146
00:14:25,978 --> 00:14:28,001
Need a hand?

147
00:14:28,077 --> 00:14:29,809
Let's do it.

148
00:15:29,886 --> 00:15:34,255
Sooner or later,
everybody's dreams go up in smoke.

149
00:15:34,988 --> 00:15:37,219
What about my dreams?

150
00:15:37,291 --> 00:15:39,556
I can't settle down, Ann.

151
00:15:39,628 --> 00:15:42,189
- We don't have to marry.
- I can't.

152
00:15:42,265 --> 00:15:45,394
I gotta be free.
I'm an artist.

153
00:15:45,469 --> 00:15:47,734
I thought you liked me.

154
00:15:49,106 --> 00:15:51,040
We have fun.

155
00:15:51,108 --> 00:15:55,102
I took you to the dump.
I let you shoot my gun at some rats.

156
00:15:55,180 --> 00:15:58,584
Shootin' rats at the dump
is not my idea of a good time.

157
00:15:58,652 --> 00:16:00,984
Why not?
We brought sandwiches.

158
00:16:01,054 --> 00:16:04,752
And sittin' at the railroads watchin'
trains, that's pretty strange too.

159
00:16:04,826 --> 00:16:08,558
See? That's what I mean.

160
00:16:08,630 --> 00:16:12,588
What I like to do, what you like to do,
ain't the same thing.

161
00:16:12,666 --> 00:16:14,465
That's not it, Emmet.

162
00:16:14,536 --> 00:16:16,628
It's that you keep
your feelings locked up...

163
00:16:16,705 --> 00:16:19,540
and you can't feel nothin'
for anybody else.

164
00:16:19,610 --> 00:16:21,771
You say that
like it's a bad thing.

165
00:16:21,846 --> 00:16:26,546
Some terrible things happen
to people in love. I know. I've seen it.

166
00:16:26,618 --> 00:16:29,917
I enjoy the company of women.
I love 'em.

167
00:16:29,988 --> 00:16:33,355
It's just that
I don't need 'em.

168
00:16:33,425 --> 00:16:37,363
I guess, you know, that's the way it is
when you're a true artist.

169
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:42,500
It doesn't mean
we can't fool around.

170
00:16:42,569 --> 00:16:46,267
Oh, right.
Or shoot rats or watch trains.

171
00:16:46,341 --> 00:16:50,539
I never met anybody that
keeps their feelings so locked up.

172
00:16:50,612 --> 00:16:53,411
I let my feelin's
come out in my music.

173
00:16:53,482 --> 00:16:57,886
Maybe if you let your feelings out in
real life, your music would be better.

174
00:16:57,954 --> 00:16:59,614
Don't talk.

175
00:17:03,528 --> 00:17:06,156
Emmet met Hattie in New Jersey.

176
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:09,257
The band was playing a resort hotel.

177
00:17:09,334 --> 00:17:12,064
On a day off, Emmet...

178
00:17:12,137 --> 00:17:15,869
and his drummer,
Bill Shields...

179
00:17:15,942 --> 00:17:18,433
were doing their
version of charm.

180
00:17:18,510 --> 00:17:21,572
They were trying to pick up girls
on the boardwalk.

181
00:17:24,986 --> 00:17:27,715
This place is heaven on earth.
Cotton candy, eight o'clock.

182
00:17:27,788 --> 00:17:29,380
Watch me work.

183
00:17:30,325 --> 00:17:32,817
Mary! Right?

184
00:17:32,895 --> 00:17:35,328
Why don't you drop dead, jerk?

185
00:17:35,397 --> 00:17:39,266
I thought you were someone I knew.
Sometimes I hit with a... Mary!

186
00:17:39,335 --> 00:17:41,064
Martina. Mary Ann.

187
00:17:41,137 --> 00:17:43,039
Marge. Kate?

188
00:17:43,107 --> 00:17:46,337
Excuse me, miss.
I'm a photography buff myself.

189
00:17:46,410 --> 00:17:49,505
I was thinkin' maybe we could
get my friend to take a picture of us.

190
00:17:49,581 --> 00:17:51,516
Wait a minute. Time out.

191
00:17:51,584 --> 00:17:53,849
- Do you see this?
- Oh, yeah.

192
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:56,786
Did you see? She looked
right at me. She smiled.

193
00:17:56,856 --> 00:17:59,951
- That was a smile.
- And she was lookin' right at me.

194
00:18:00,026 --> 00:18:01,492
Which one you want?

195
00:18:01,561 --> 00:18:03,392
The little one
with the silly hat.

196
00:18:03,463 --> 00:18:05,397
She's more my size.
I'll flip you.

197
00:18:05,466 --> 00:18:07,660
- I saw her first!
- All right!

198
00:18:07,734 --> 00:18:10,204
You want the little one?
Take the little one.

199
00:18:10,272 --> 00:18:12,297
I'll take the redhead.
What difference does it make?

200
00:18:12,373 --> 00:18:15,811
They're gettin' away. There's
nothin' wrong with the little one.

201
00:18:15,879 --> 00:18:18,746
The redhead's got
nice legs and a nice chest.

202
00:18:18,815 --> 00:18:20,943
- I'll take the redhead.
- The little one is cute.

203
00:18:21,018 --> 00:18:24,976
She has a nice face and those Cupid-bow
lips I like, but I'll take the redhead.

204
00:18:25,054 --> 00:18:26,718
- You wanted the little one.
- I changed my mind.

205
00:18:26,792 --> 00:18:28,383
I'll flip you.

206
00:18:30,596 --> 00:18:32,257
- Call.
- Tails.

207
00:18:35,634 --> 00:18:37,866
- I got the little one.
- We agree.

208
00:18:37,938 --> 00:18:40,337
- Now they gotta agree.
- Come on.

209
00:18:41,842 --> 00:18:44,902
I'm telling you, you're gonna
get on the Ferris wheel this time.

210
00:18:44,978 --> 00:18:48,780
Remember when you tried to go on?
Last year we tried to get you up there.

211
00:18:48,851 --> 00:18:50,785
- Excuse me.
- You were scared.

212
00:18:50,853 --> 00:18:54,153
Hi. You ladies from around here?

213
00:18:54,224 --> 00:18:56,384
Yeah, we work right near here.

214
00:18:56,458 --> 00:18:59,155
I'm Billy Shields.
I'm a musician.

215
00:18:59,229 --> 00:19:02,221
He's with my quintet.
I'm Emmet Ray.

216
00:19:02,299 --> 00:19:04,735
The Emmet Ray Hot Quintet.
We're at the Lakeside Ballroom.

217
00:19:04,803 --> 00:19:08,828
It's our day off, so we were thinking
maybe you could show us the sights.

218
00:19:08,905 --> 00:19:11,842
- You wanna go watch some trains?
- What?

219
00:19:11,910 --> 00:19:14,938
He's kidding.
Let's go for a drink.

220
00:19:16,449 --> 00:19:19,214
Ask him. I liked you instantly.
I'm bein' honest.

221
00:19:19,286 --> 00:19:21,448
We flipped, he won, I got you.

222
00:19:21,523 --> 00:19:23,854
I'm Gracie MacRae.

223
00:19:23,924 --> 00:19:25,355
Billy Shields.

224
00:19:25,427 --> 00:19:29,523
And if I may say, you have the most
beautiful blue eyes I've ever seen.

225
00:19:29,597 --> 00:19:31,965
This is my friend Hattie.

226
00:19:32,035 --> 00:19:34,229
Hattie, I'm Emmet Ray.

227
00:19:34,303 --> 00:19:37,671
I've got the quintet.
You like jazz music, baby?

228
00:19:37,741 --> 00:19:40,539
How about we take
a boat ride, huh?

229
00:19:40,611 --> 00:19:43,274
Well, sure.
We'd love to.

230
00:19:43,349 --> 00:19:45,873
