- You give it away.

544
00:49:24,035 --> 00:49:26,469
You drink it up.
You pick up checks.

545
00:49:26,539 --> 00:49:29,735
You lose it in poolrooms, and
you're always buyin' Hattie presents.

546
00:49:29,810 --> 00:49:32,642
She's like a kid. She loves
tearin' the paper off the box.

547
00:49:32,712 --> 00:49:34,303
You gotta go on a budget.

548
00:49:34,379 --> 00:49:36,405
I'll go on a budget
if someone will straighten me out.

549
00:49:36,482 --> 00:49:38,473
A budget's not easy
for a guy like you.

550
00:49:38,551 --> 00:49:41,987
- When I set my mind to somethin'...
- You fight every good idea I have.

551
00:49:42,054 --> 00:49:44,282
I'll go on a budget.
I'll be good.

552
00:49:44,355 --> 00:49:46,882
What do you spend on clothes a year?
Do you have any idea?

553
00:49:46,959 --> 00:49:48,653
Want me to look like a bum?

554
00:49:48,726 --> 00:49:51,856
- What about rent?
- I don't know. It's all hotels.

555
00:49:51,931 --> 00:49:54,592
- Any idea what you spend on food?
- The booze gratis?

556
00:49:54,667 --> 00:49:59,127
Help yourself. Do you have any idea
what you spend on food or entertainment?

557
00:49:59,204 --> 00:50:02,264
Do you have any investments,
anything that'll throw off revenue?

558
00:50:02,338 --> 00:50:05,707
I got some savings,
mostly from Hattie takin' in laundry.

559
00:50:05,777 --> 00:50:08,976
Emmet, we gotta look
for places to cut down.

560
00:50:09,049 --> 00:50:12,208
I burned a hundred dollars once.
A guy dared me. He was a four-flusher.

561
00:50:12,282 --> 00:50:14,341
He burned a fifty,
I burned a hundred.

562
00:50:14,418 --> 00:50:18,046
He burned a twenty, I burned
another hundred. I could cut that out.

563
00:50:18,122 --> 00:50:20,920
You wanna end up
in the poorhouse when you're old?

564
00:50:20,991 --> 00:50:23,323
You ever see a poorhouse?

565
00:50:23,394 --> 00:50:26,522
From now on, your salary
and expenses will come to me.

566
00:50:26,598 --> 00:50:28,962
I'm puttin' you on an allowance.

567
00:50:29,032 --> 00:50:31,051
Okay, that's it.
The party's over.

568
00:50:31,052 --> 00:50:33,069
Okay, that's it.
The party's over.

569
00:50:33,137 --> 00:50:37,539
You're spendin' too much,
so now we've gotta go on a budget.

570
00:50:37,607 --> 00:50:41,442
Now, aside from food,
what are your expenses?

571
00:50:42,280 --> 00:50:45,008
What about the doctor bills?
You got a doctor?

572
00:50:45,081 --> 00:50:47,950
I bet you I get you
a veterinarian who's cheaper.

573
00:50:48,019 --> 00:50:50,211
And this is goin' out.

574
00:50:51,386 --> 00:50:53,651
What are we?
The electric company?

575
00:50:54,458 --> 00:50:57,185
We gotta save every penny.

576
00:50:58,362 --> 00:50:59,795
What is that?

577
00:51:05,468 --> 00:51:07,730
You remembered my birthday?

578
00:51:10,474 --> 00:51:12,407
We can't afford presents.

579
00:51:13,541 --> 00:51:16,602
That's gotta go back.
It's gotta go back.

580
00:51:23,251 --> 00:51:25,777
These are the kid gloves
I really wanted.

581
00:51:29,724 --> 00:51:32,421
Exactly the gloves
I wanted, these are.

582
00:51:35,897 --> 00:51:38,420
You know what I'm gonna do?
I'm gonna cut you a break.

583
00:51:38,500 --> 00:51:41,024
It's my birthday and...

584
00:51:41,101 --> 00:51:43,536
So I'm gonna let you
give 'em to me.

585
00:51:47,743 --> 00:51:49,676
You made this yourself?

586
00:51:56,448 --> 00:51:58,714
Your writin' looks like a chicken.

587
00:51:59,854 --> 00:52:03,255
Let's see.
"It's been almost a year...

588
00:52:03,325 --> 00:52:06,088
since we've been together."

589
00:52:06,160 --> 00:52:07,649
Ayear?

590
00:52:08,727 --> 00:52:11,219
Well, that's scary.

591
00:52:16,638 --> 00:52:18,695
What's this word here?

592
00:52:19,974 --> 00:52:22,406
Is that... Is that "love"?

593
00:52:25,077 --> 00:52:28,535
Oh, no. Don't go gettin'
any big ideas here.

594
00:52:28,615 --> 00:52:30,047
Jesus.

595
00:52:32,486 --> 00:52:34,644
I must've ate somethin' bad.

596
00:52:37,323 --> 00:52:39,757
I'm feelin'...
I'm gonna be sick.

597
00:52:46,497 --> 00:52:48,932
- Got somethin' for me today, Mr. Ray?
- I don't.

598
00:52:49,000 --> 00:52:51,935
- Mr. Ray, it's me, Charlie.
- I'm all tapped out.

599
00:52:52,003 --> 00:52:54,406
- You never let me down.
- Look.

600
00:52:54,474 --> 00:52:57,532
I'd like to help you,
but I'm on a budget.

601
00:52:57,608 --> 00:52:59,634
I haven't had
a bowl of soup all day.

602
00:52:59,712 --> 00:53:02,144
What, you wanna make me feel bad?

603
00:53:03,882 --> 00:53:06,851
- That's all you get.
- All right, thanks.

604
00:53:06,919 --> 00:53:09,079
Thanks, Mr. Ray.

605
00:53:09,155 --> 00:53:12,520
What's the urgency?
I came here as quick as I could.

606
00:53:12,590 --> 00:53:16,252
- Would you look at this thing?
- This is why I came quick to meet you?

607
00:53:16,326 --> 00:53:18,657
- He only wants 4,000 for it.
- Yeah, so?

608
00:53:18,727 --> 00:53:20,390
Does it fit the budget?

609
00:53:20,464 --> 00:53:22,932
Are you kidding?
We just sold one of your cars.

610
00:53:22,999 --> 00:53:25,869
I'm tryin' to unload
the other one, not buy one.

611
00:53:25,938 --> 00:53:27,528
- If I cut down?
- Cut down?

612
00:53:27,604 --> 00:53:31,132
- Where are you gonna get four grand?
- I'll borrow the money and pay it off.

613
00:53:31,209 --> 00:53:34,609
No one will lend you that kind of money,
and you'll be saddled with payments.

614
00:53:34,678 --> 00:53:36,874
- I want the car.
- No, Emmet.

615
00:53:36,948 --> 00:53:39,040
Hattie will give up desserts.

616
00:53:39,115 --> 00:53:41,547
- I want the car.
- It's out of the question.

617
00:53:41,616 --> 00:53:44,109
- I gotta have the car.
- You don't have the money.

618
00:53:44,188 --> 00:53:47,783
- I gotta have the car.
- There's no way!

619
00:53:47,858 --> 00:53:50,656
- We can't afford it.
- Stop sayin' "we."

620
00:53:50,727 --> 00:53:53,060
If I want the car,
I'm gonna get it.

621
00:53:53,130 --> 00:53:56,119
- Maybe someday, if it's in your budget.
- Budget! Budget!

622
00:53:56,198 --> 00:53:59,636
