00:54:07,076 --> 00:54:08,188
He said it, but he didn't believe it.

627
00:54:08,189 --> 00:54:09,301
He said it, but he didn't believe it.

628
00:54:09,376 --> 00:54:13,108
I mean, in his soul,
he worshipped Django Reinhardt.

629
00:54:13,181 --> 00:54:15,616
It was more than that.
He was frozen by him.

630
00:54:15,685 --> 00:54:18,016
Django was like a god to him.

631
00:54:18,087 --> 00:54:20,885
I don't know if this is true,
or just another Emmet Ray story...

632
00:54:20,957 --> 00:54:24,617
but Sid Bishop, who was trying
to help him financially at the time...

633
00:54:24,692 --> 00:54:28,355
got him a job in this club,
and one night, just before show time...

634
00:54:28,429 --> 00:54:31,832
one of the guys backstage
decides to play a joke on him...

635
00:54:31,901 --> 00:54:33,959
and tells him this lie.

636
00:54:34,035 --> 00:54:36,230
Hey, Emmet!

637
00:54:36,304 --> 00:54:40,332
Emmet, you're not gonna believe it.
Guess who's sittin' at the front table?

638
00:54:40,408 --> 00:54:42,875
Django Reinhardt.

639
00:54:42,944 --> 00:54:47,209
Are you kiddin' me? We should
get him up on stage with you.

640
00:54:47,281 --> 00:54:49,444
Reinhardt.

641
00:54:49,517 --> 00:54:51,883
He's gonna show him up.

642
00:54:51,953 --> 00:54:54,581
- I'm gonna...
- Come on.

643
00:54:54,656 --> 00:54:57,590
Emmet, we can get him
up on stage with us.

644
00:55:01,329 --> 00:55:04,262
- Django Reinhardt's here.
- Really?

645
00:55:10,773 --> 00:55:13,295
Hey, Django's not in the audience.

646
00:55:13,372 --> 00:55:16,536
The house is half-empty. There's
just some guy that looks like Django.

647
00:55:16,609 --> 00:55:19,170
Let's see if he's got
the nerve to come down.

648
00:55:19,245 --> 00:55:21,738
- Harry, let's go.
- Emmet, we're on!

649
00:55:21,815 --> 00:55:23,908
We should do it anyway.

650
00:55:25,016 --> 00:55:28,316
Emmet, come on down.
I'll wait for you.

651
00:55:28,387 --> 00:55:31,880
I'll take you to the front table myself.
I'll introduce you to Django.

652
00:55:31,959 --> 00:55:33,984
Now, as the story goes...

653
00:55:34,061 --> 00:55:37,963
Emmet, as you know, was pathologically
phobic about Django Reinhardt...

654
00:55:38,032 --> 00:55:40,726
so he tried to escape
through the roof.

655
00:55:40,800 --> 00:55:42,791
He just figured,
to hell with the job that night.

656
00:55:42,869 --> 00:55:46,963
But remember, this was a guy
who had fainted twice...

657
00:55:47,038 --> 00:55:50,099
when he came face-to-face
with Django Reinhardt in Europe.

658
00:55:50,176 --> 00:55:54,613
He's looking for a way out, and decides
to jump to the building next door.

659
00:55:54,680 --> 00:55:58,809
Well, as fate would have it,
he hits a weak spot in the roof...

660
00:55:58,882 --> 00:56:01,943
and crashes through
into somebody's apartment.

661
00:56:02,019 --> 00:56:05,616
As it happened, the apartment was
being used by some counterfeiters...

662
00:56:05,690 --> 00:56:09,056
who thought it was a raid when
he came through the roof, and ran out.

663
00:57:18,395 --> 00:57:21,157
Well, Eddie Durham,
the great jazz pioneer...

664
00:57:21,229 --> 00:57:24,097
met Emmet in Chicago in the 1930's.

665
00:57:24,167 --> 00:57:26,190
Here's what he said
about him in his book.

666
00:57:26,268 --> 00:57:29,260
"I met Emmet in Chicago.
It was the height of the Depression.

667
00:57:29,337 --> 00:57:33,775
Work was scarce. A lot of guys
took on teaching music as a sideline.

668
00:57:33,843 --> 00:57:35,434
Emmet refused.

669
00:57:35,510 --> 00:57:39,275
At that time he was married
to a woman named Blanche."

670
00:58:42,142 --> 00:58:44,303
- What are you doing?
- What?

671
00:58:44,377 --> 00:58:45,006
Nothing.

672
00:58:45,007 --> 00:58:45,637
Nothing.

673
00:58:45,712 --> 00:58:48,111
Excuse me, darling.

674
00:58:48,181 --> 00:58:50,116
You were stealing that box.

675
00:58:50,184 --> 00:58:52,913
- No.
- Oh, yes, you were. I saw you.

676
00:58:52,986 --> 00:58:55,319
Why?

677
00:58:55,389 --> 00:58:56,719
I don't know.

678
00:58:56,790 --> 00:58:58,915
You're a genius, you know?

679
00:58:58,991 --> 00:59:02,119
Eubie Blake thinks I'm the best guitar
player in the whole world, bar none.

680
00:59:02,194 --> 00:59:04,526
- And he knows Django.
- Truly?

681
00:59:04,596 --> 00:59:06,531
I'm Blanche Williams.

682
00:59:07,967 --> 00:59:11,164
- Are you gonna squeal on me?
- "Squeal" on you?

683
00:59:14,137 --> 00:59:17,404
Gosh. Not only are you
vain and egotistical...

684
00:59:17,476 --> 00:59:20,739
but you have genuine crudeness.

685
00:59:21,812 --> 00:59:23,747
I didn't want the goddamn thing.

686
00:59:25,582 --> 00:59:28,075
I won't squeal on you
if you take me for a drive...

687
00:59:28,153 --> 00:59:31,211
in that sublime automobile
of yours.

688
00:59:31,288 --> 00:59:32,756
Drive.

689
00:59:32,823 --> 00:59:34,451
Where?

690
00:59:34,526 --> 00:59:37,493
To the ends of the earth.
Astonish me.

691
00:59:42,966 --> 00:59:44,663
It's fun, isn't it?

692
00:59:44,737 --> 00:59:46,929
Well, it's definitely different.

693
00:59:47,003 --> 00:59:49,668
Make sure you don't pull it.
You squeeze it.

694
00:59:49,741 --> 00:59:51,672
Squeeze the trigger.

695
00:59:52,741 --> 00:59:55,769
- Do you do this often?
- Every chance I get.

696
00:59:55,845 --> 00:59:58,006
Specifically, what's the thrill?

697
00:59:58,081 --> 01:00:01,314
Well, I'm not sure, really.
There's one.

698
01:00:01,385 --> 01:00:04,182
And you got him!

699
01:00:04,254 --> 01:00:08,088
Do you get a bigger kick
doing this or stealing small objects?

700
01:00:08,158 --> 01:00:10,283
You know what?
I could really use a drink.

701
01:00:22,937 --> 01:00:25,963
I stop in here every time
I come through Chicago.

702
01:00:26,041 --> 01:00:27,976
She makes great chili.

703
01:00:28,044 --> 01:00:30,637
You like chili?

704
01:00:30,713 --> 01:00:33,180
What do you think of
when you play?

705
01:00:33,248 --> 01:00:35,309
What goes through your mind?

706
01:00:35,386 --> 01:00:37,317
What are your real feelings?

707
01:00:38,785 --> 01:00:41,346
I don't know.
That I'm underpaid.

708
01:00:41,422 --> 01:00:43,753
I think about that sometimes.

709
01:00:43,824 --> 01:00:45,920
Tell me about the girl
you lived with.

710
01:00:49,030 --> 01:00:51,659
She was nice, but I told her
not to fall in love with me.

711
01:00:51,735 --> 01:00:53,668
It was very one-sided.

712
01:00:55,404 --> 01:00:57,803
She was nice, but I just
cut out one night.

713
