950
01:16:18,896 --> 01:16:21,657
have gone to bed with each other,
that they're lovers.

951
01:16:21,729 --> 01:16:24,255
And he's consumed with rage.

952
01:16:24,332 --> 01:16:29,327
Now, just at that moment,
Torrio decides to pull off the road...

953
01:16:29,405 --> 01:16:32,065
and go into a gas station
to buy some cigarettes.

954
01:16:32,139 --> 01:16:35,302
And there's Emmet
in the back of the car...

955
01:16:35,376 --> 01:16:38,242
and he's trying very hard to
figure out who he wants to shoot.

956
01:16:38,311 --> 01:16:41,076
Does he want to shoot Blanche?
Torrio?

957
01:16:41,148 --> 01:16:42,808
Should he shoot
both of them together?

958
01:16:42,882 --> 01:16:45,045
He's working on this problem.

959
01:16:45,120 --> 01:16:49,146
They go into the store,
and exactly at that moment...

960
01:16:49,222 --> 01:16:51,157
a holdup is taking place.

961
01:16:51,226 --> 01:16:55,754
Two guys come running out.
They don't know what to do.

962
01:16:55,831 --> 01:16:58,229
All hell is breaking loose.
There's gunshots.

963
01:16:58,299 --> 01:17:00,288
Instead of taking their car...

964
01:17:00,365 --> 01:17:03,928
Torrio's got a big car.
They jump in that and pull off.

965
01:17:19,919 --> 01:17:21,977
Calling all cars.

966
01:17:46,045 --> 01:17:47,409
I'm Emmet Ray.

967
01:17:47,479 --> 01:17:49,915
I'm the greatest guitar player
in the world.

968
01:17:49,983 --> 01:17:52,508
Except maybe this gypsy.

969
01:17:52,585 --> 01:17:56,247
Perhaps you heard my recording of
"You Were Meant For Me," RCA Victor.

970
01:17:57,489 --> 01:18:00,684
You were meant for me

971
01:18:01,960 --> 01:18:03,010
That's not what I heard.

972
01:18:03,011 --> 01:18:04,061
That's not what I heard.

973
01:18:04,129 --> 01:18:06,462
But like all Emmet Ray stories...

974
01:18:06,531 --> 01:18:10,159
you never know what's made up,
exaggerated, true.

975
01:18:10,234 --> 01:18:13,397
You never know what to believe.
What I heard was this.

976
01:18:13,471 --> 01:18:16,439
I heard that when they
pulled into the gas station...

977
01:18:16,506 --> 01:18:18,875
Blanche gets out
to get some cigarettes...

978
01:18:18,945 --> 01:18:20,876
and that's
when he confronted them.

979
01:18:22,345 --> 01:18:25,908
How could you? How could you
cheat on me with a bum like that?

980
01:18:25,984 --> 01:18:27,006
Emmet, don't!

981
01:18:27,084 --> 01:18:29,246
Make a fool out of me
in front of everybody!

982
01:18:29,321 --> 01:18:32,345
So I slept with him.
But I was just researching a book!

983
01:18:32,421 --> 01:18:33,890
I loved you!

984
01:18:35,326 --> 01:18:37,259
Don't be crazy. Do something!

985
01:18:39,496 --> 01:18:43,023
I'm sorry. My tire blew out.

986
01:18:43,100 --> 01:18:47,432
Believe me, he never tried to kill
himself, because Emmet Ray was...

987
01:18:47,503 --> 01:18:50,906
He had much too much ego
for anything like that.

988
01:18:52,709 --> 01:18:54,733
A story that Eddie Condon
tells about...

989
01:18:54,810 --> 01:18:57,246
And Eddie Condon definitely
was not a reliable source...

990
01:18:57,314 --> 01:18:59,543
'cause he was
a big embellisher himself.

991
01:18:59,615 --> 01:19:03,518
But the story Eddie Condon tells,
I believe...

992
01:19:03,586 --> 01:19:06,348
is that Torrio was aware...

993
01:19:06,422 --> 01:19:10,256
that the fact that he was a gangster
was a big turn- on for Blanche.

994
01:19:10,326 --> 01:19:11,371
And so he decided...

995
01:19:11,372 --> 01:19:12,417
And so he decided...

996
01:19:12,495 --> 01:19:15,588
that he would
pull into this gas station...

997
01:19:15,665 --> 01:19:17,597
and he would stick it up.

998
01:19:23,004 --> 01:19:25,940
- Can I help you, sir?
- Get your hands in the air, Pops.

999
01:19:26,008 --> 01:19:27,668
Give me everything
in the register!

1000
01:19:27,743 --> 01:19:30,713
Emmet was so panicked
by hearing gunshots...

1001
01:19:30,780 --> 01:19:33,748
he crept into the front seat
and took off.

1002
01:19:33,815 --> 01:19:38,514
He didn't get more than 50 feet
before he crashed into an oncoming car.

1003
01:19:38,586 --> 01:19:43,023
Now there's this terrible crash.
Miraculously, no one is hurt.

1004
01:19:43,091 --> 01:19:46,790
And who gets out of the car
but a group of musicians.

1005
01:19:46,862 --> 01:19:48,795
I can't remember who it was.

1006
01:19:48,863 --> 01:19:52,561
It was like Buck Clayton, Coleman
Hawkins, Teddy Wilson or something.

1007
01:19:52,634 --> 01:19:56,730
But there, suddenly,
standing in front of Emmet...

1008
01:19:56,805 --> 01:19:58,736
is Django Reinhardt.

1009
01:20:13,187 --> 01:20:15,781
I believe later that year...

1010
01:20:15,857 --> 01:20:18,381
Emmet turned up in New Jersey...

1011
01:20:18,458 --> 01:20:22,826
and made that recording he did
of one of his own compositions.

1012
01:20:22,894 --> 01:20:24,625
"Unfaithful Woman."

1013
01:20:49,021 --> 01:20:50,715
Very good, everybody.

1014
01:20:50,789 --> 01:20:53,555
- Particularly me.
- That was great. And me.

1015
01:20:53,627 --> 01:20:57,256
- Let's go get somethin' to eat.
- Emmet, we're going to New York.

1016
01:20:57,330 --> 01:21:01,025
We're goin' to New York.
The big money.

1017
01:21:01,099 --> 01:21:03,091
Can I get those cigarettes?

1018
01:21:03,168 --> 01:21:07,194
Em, I tell you, the music business
really picked up, just like you said.

1019
01:21:07,270 --> 01:21:10,729
We got some dancers lined up for
tonight, pretty ones. They are wild.

1020
01:22:01,258 --> 01:22:03,192
How are you?

1021
01:22:06,295 --> 01:22:08,230
You look healthy.

1022
01:22:12,168 --> 01:22:15,331
I'm in town makin' a record.

1023
01:22:15,404 --> 01:22:18,235
I wrote a beautiful tune.
It's a classic.

1024
01:22:21,511 --> 01:22:23,445
I'm sorry I cut out
on you like that.

1025
01:22:24,948 --> 01:22:27,314
It was time to move on.

1026
01:22:27,384 --> 01:22:29,874
I was fair. I told you
not to fall in love with me.

1027
01:22:29,951 --> 01:22:32,442
It's nothin' personal.

1028
01:22:32,521 --> 01:22:34,579
It's just, I'm an artist.

1029
01:22:38,194 --> 01:22:40,925
I like women,
but they gotta have their place.

1030
01:22:45,099 --> 01:22:46,693
You angry with me?

1031
01:22:48,870 --> 01:22:50,496
You have every right to be.

1032
01:22:50,571 --> 01:22:52,540
I don't hold it against you.

1033
01:22:53,709 --> 01:22:55,902
I even thought of you
a couple of times.

1034
01:22:58,813 --> 01:23:01,336
My wife said...

1035
01:23:01,415 --> 01:23:03,406
I said your name once
in my sleep.

1036
01:23:07,289 --> 01:23:09,223
Must have had a nightmare
or somethin'.

1037
01:23:12,058 --> 01:23:13,720
Yeah.

1038
01:23:13,794 --> 01:23:17,822
I had a wife. She's gone now,
and believe me, I don't miss her.

1039
01:23:17,898 --> 01:23:20,061
I don't mean to say
I miss you either...

1040
01:23:20,136 --> 01:23:22,498
but I didn't have
any bad feelings about you.

1041
01:23:26,372 --> 01:23:29,772
We got a real good contract at a club
in New York for a year. Good dough.

1042
01:23:36,050 --> 01:23:39,143
Maybe you'd like to come.

1043
01:23:39,219 --> 01:23:40,684
You know?

1044
01:23:40,751 --> 01:23:43,347
I'm not makin' any promises, but...

1045
01:23:43,423 --> 01:23:45,822
I think you might have fun.

1046
01:23:45,890 --> 01:23:50,191
You'd be in New York with...

1047
01:23:50,262 --> 01:23:53,130
one of the two best
guitar players in the world...

1048
01:23:54,934 --> 01:23:57,163
six best poker players.

1049
01:23:57,234 --> 01:23:59,169
Not countin' that.

1050
01:24:01,572 --> 01:24:03,508
We leave tomorrow, if you want.

1051
01:24:03,576 --> 01:24:05,476
If you don't, I understand.

1052
01:24:05,545 --> 01:24:09,003
You know? Then it'd be
"It was nice seeing you again.

1053
01:24:09,082 --> 01:24:10,516
Good luck."

1054
01:24:13,085 --> 01:24:15,019
I never could
get your handwritin'.

1055
01:24:25,264 --> 01:24:26,696
Happily?

1056
01:24:29,266 --> 01:24:30,699
Got kids?

1057
01:24:35,206 --> 01:24:36,640
Boy or girl?

1058
01:24:38,541 --> 01:24:40,567
Boy?

1059
01:24:40,644 --> 01:24:42,077
Girl?

1060
01:24:47,051 --> 01:24:48,984
It's just as well.

1061
01:24:50,454 --> 01:24:53,855
I wouldn't want to give you the wrong
impression. You'd get attached to me.

1062
01:24:53,923 --> 01:24:56,357
And you know me.
I can't take entanglements.

1063
01:25:00,130 --> 01:25:03,931
I gotta go. We're gonna take
some chorus girls out tonight.

1064
01:25:04,001 --> 01:25:05,936
And I'm leavin' tomorrow.

1065
01:25:09,806 --> 01:25:11,739
Take it easy.

1066
01:26:09,064 --> 01:26:14,125
I'm the greatest solo instrumentalist
on the guitar you'll ever hear.

1067
01:26:14,201 --> 01:26:15,134
Oh, yeah?

1068
01:26:15,203 --> 01:26:18,898
The public's just getting to know my
name. Next year, I'll be in the money.

1069
01:26:20,943 --> 01:26:23,966
You're a real looker.
You are a real looker.

1070
01:26:24,043 --> 01:26:27,275
- You're not that bad yourself.
- I mean it!

1071
01:26:27,347 --> 01:26:30,747
Maybe that's why the men give me
a lot of tips when I dance.

1072
01:26:30,816 --> 01:26:32,615
You wanna go watch trains?

1073
01:26:32,687 --> 01:26:34,152
What?

1074
01:26:34,220 --> 01:26:35,744
- Come on.
- Trains?

1075
01:26:35,823 --> 01:26:37,313
Wait. Where are we going?

1076
01:26:37,391 --> 01:26:40,291
- Jesus.
- Outta the way.

1077
01:26:40,360 --> 01:26:42,760
Grab my stuff. Jesus.

1078
01:26:42,827 --> 01:26:45,194
- Where are we going?
- My cigarettes!

1079
01:26:45,264 --> 01:26:47,324
Where do you think
you're taking me?

1080
01:26:50,636 --> 01:26:52,400
Where's my cigarettes?

1081
01:26:52,472 --> 01:26:54,440
Leave them alone.
Let's just go.

1082
01:26:56,175 --> 01:26:59,044
Come on.
Let's go watch trains.

1083
01:27:15,662 --> 01:27:18,926
You almost lost me there, you know.
Did you see that?

1084
01:27:20,030 --> 01:27:22,557
Jesus. What are we doing here?

1085
01:27:22,634 --> 01:27:24,568
I like to sit out...

1086
01:27:25,838 --> 01:27:27,930
and look at the trains pass.

1087
01:27:28,006 --> 01:27:30,530
Yeah. To each his own, I say.

1088
01:27:30,606 --> 01:27:32,633
I mean, I don't understand it.

1089
01:27:32,711 --> 01:27:36,041
I can make my guitar
sound like a train.

1090
01:27:36,112 --> 01:27:39,050
God! I mean, I'm a nice girl.

1091
01:27:39,117 --> 01:27:41,584
I don't understand
why you'd bring me here.

1092
01:27:41,653 --> 01:27:46,022
I can make my guitar
sound just like a train.

1093
01:27:46,090 --> 01:27:49,287
I got a warm room we can go to.

1094
01:27:49,360 --> 01:27:51,553
Come on. I'll take care of you.

1095
01:27:51,627 --> 01:27:54,689
Come on. It's nice.

1096
01:27:54,766 --> 01:27:59,669
Jesus, I don't understand why you would
bring a nice girl like me out here.

1097
01:28:02,104 --> 01:28:04,130
I'm takin' requests.

1098
01:28:04,208 --> 01:28:06,142
Do you know "Sweet Sue"?

1099
01:29:44,638 --> 01:29:47,468
All right, are you finished?
Can we go now?

1100
01:29:47,539 --> 01:29:50,738
I really have to pee, you know.
I gotta go to the bathroom.

1101
01:29:52,379 --> 01:29:54,109
- What's the matter with you?
- Go on.

1102
01:29:54,182 --> 01:29:55,512
- What?
- Get outta here.

1103
01:29:55,582 --> 01:29:58,174
What? What are you talk...

1104
01:29:58,250 --> 01:30:00,776
- You dragged me out here.
- Just leave me alone.

1105
01:30:00,853 --> 01:30:02,582
- What?
- Leave me alone!

1106
01:30:02,654 --> 01:30:06,056
I don't need anybody!

1107
01:30:06,125 --> 01:30:09,685
- I made a mistake!
- Yeah. I'll say.

1108
01:30:09,762 --> 01:30:11,195
I made mistake!

1109
01:30:39,458 --> 01:30:41,982
I have no idea
what happened to Emmet Ray.

1110
01:30:42,059 --> 01:30:45,722
He just sort of disappeared,
I guess.

1111
01:30:45,796 --> 01:30:48,526
He did make, though,
in those last couple of years...

1112
01:30:48,599 --> 01:30:51,068
he made really
his best recordings.

1113
01:30:51,135 --> 01:30:53,796
He never played more beautifully,
more movingly.

1114
01:30:55,606 --> 01:30:58,039
Something just seemed
to kind of open up in him.

1115
01:30:58,108 --> 01:31:00,976
It was amazing,
because he was, finally...

1116
01:31:01,045 --> 01:31:03,274
every bit as good
as Django Reinhardt.

1117
01:31:03,346 --> 01:31:07,374
And then he just, you know,
seemed to fade away.

1118
01:31:07,451 --> 01:31:09,384
I mean, I have no idea.

1119
01:31:10,420 --> 01:31:12,388
Some people said
he went to Europe.

1120
01:31:12,456 --> 01:31:17,121
And some people feel that he may
have stopped playing altogether.

1121
01:31:17,195 --> 01:31:21,823
But we do have, fortunately,
those last recordings he made.

1122
01:31:24,299 --> 01:31:27,600
And they're great.
They're absolutely beautiful.

